 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, July 24: Air-India has appointed a consortium led by Accenture as consultant for its proposed merger with Indian, formerly known as Indian Airlines. A committee, set up by the civil aviation ministry for the merger, has taken this decision at its meeting today. ?The details of the terms and reference were provided to the consultant, which include both pre-merger and post-merger issues,? sources said.

 New Delhi, July 24: The Hinduja group has bought Iveco?s stake in the UK-based LRLIH Ltd to make it a fully-owned subsidiary, thus increasing its holding in group company Ashok Leyland to 51 per cent.

 Mumbai, July 24: Escorts has posted a profit after tax of Rs 1.57 crore for the quarter ended June 30, compared with a loss after tax of Rs 57.38 crore for the same quarter in 2005-06. Total income rose 94.79 per cent to Rs 478.50 crore from Rs 245.64 crore.

 New Delhi, July 24: Morepen?s Rs 750-crore corporate debt restructuring proposal involving more than 30 banks has been approved by the empowered group.

 New Delhi, July 24: Essar Oil has reopened about 350 petrol pumps it was forced to shut down after it suffered heavy losses as it tried to match its petrol and diesel prices with hugely-subsidised public sector rates.




